@F msg.flow v1.0 2026-01-13
= communication > signal â€” roads between homes

intent
  send "signed" messages
  encrypt "private" content
  persist "inbox" state

logic
  send(to, content, private)
    1. resolve recipient
    2. sign (timestamp | public_key | content)
    3. if private: encrypt with recipient public_key
    4. save to recipient/messages/

  read(unread_only)
    1. scan my_enclave/messages/
    2. verify signatures
    3. if private: decrypt with my_private_key
    4. mark as read

  auth-once
    resolve sender from session if not explicit

commands
  py msg <to> "content"              | public msg
  py msg <to> --private "content"    | encrypted msg
  py msg --read [--all]              | check inbox

integration
  SovereignAgent (identity, keys)
  Ed25519 (signatures)
  OpaqueStorage (encryption)
